6/29/83 forum request: previous_unseen, pu

Syntax:  pu {trans_spec} {-control_args}


Syntax as an active request:  [pu {trans_spec} {-control_args}]


Function:
Prints or returns the transaction index of the first transaction before
the specified transaction which has not been marked as seen, or before
the current transaction if no trans_spec is given.


Arguments:
trans_spec
   is the transaction for which the previous_unseen transaction is desired.


Control arguments:
-include_deleted, -idl
   print or return the index of the previous_unseen transaction even if
   it is deleted.
-only_deleted, -odl
   print or return the index of the previous_unseen deleted transaction.
-only_non_deleted, -ondl
   print or return the index of the previous_unseen non-deleted
   transaction.  (Default)
